hin certain legible parameters.To do so, Sensual Excess analyzes moments of brown jouissance that exceed these constraints. These ruptures illuminate multiple epistemologies of selfhood and sensuality that offer frameworks for minoritarian knowledge production which is designed to enable one to sit with uncertainty. Through examinations of installations and performances like Judy Chicago’s The Dinner Party, Kara Walker’s A Subtlety, Patty Chang’s In Love and Nao Bustamante’s Neapolitan, Musser unpacks the relationships between racialized sexuality and consumption to interrogate foundational concepts in psychoanalytic theory, critical race studies, feminism, and queer theory. In so doing, Sensual Excess offers a project of knowledge production focused not on mastery, but on sensing and imagining otherwise, whatever and wherever that might be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLesbianism. 0aSexual excitement. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh  aAmber Hawk Swanson.  aAudre Lorde.  aCarrie Mae Weems.  aCheryl Dunye.  aJoan Riviere.  aJudy Chicago.  aKara Walker.  aLuce Irigaray.  aLyle Ashton Harris.  aMaureen Catbagan.  aMickalene Thomas.  aNao Bustamante.  aOedipal complex.  aPatty Chang.  aXandra Ibarra.  aabjection.  aaesthetics.  adiaspora.  adomesticity.  aemotionality.  afeminine jouissance.  afeminine misery.  afetishism.  afilipino art.  aflesh.  afriction.  ahysteria.  akinship.  alesbian feminism.  alesbian.  alistening.  amimesis.  aminoritarian.  amutual vulnerability.  anarcissism.  aperversion.  aphotography.  apornotrope.  aproprioception.  apsychoanalysis.  aracial melancholy.  aracial violation.  arhinestones.  ascalar.  aselfhood.  asensation.  asexuality.  aspirituality.  astrap-on. 